AppImage Build Instructions

Check out libgphoto2 and gphoto2 from git.

Build container image. This has been tested to work using podman, e.g.:

podman build -t gphoto-dev .

If you encounter a checksum failure after downloading the linuxdeploy appimage, manually download it from https://github.com/linuxdeploy/linuxdeploy/releases/download/continuous/linuxdeploy-x86_64.AppImage, run sha512sum on it, and manually update the Dockerfile.

Run container image, passing in host volume mounts for the source directories, e.g.:

GPHOTO2_DIR=/path/to/gphoto2
LIBGPHOTO2_DIR=/path/to/libgphoto2

podman run --interactive --tty --rm \
	-v $GPHOTO2_DIR:/workspace/gphoto2 \
	-v $LIBGPHOTO2_DIR:/workspace/libgphoto2 \
	--name gphoto-build gphoto-dev

The default command will compile libgphoto2, gphoto2, and construct the appimage. The resulting appimage will be in the gphoto2/appimage directory (the same one that this README resides in).

